items.title: Heisenberg said it was impossible. Scientists just proved otherwise
bullets: • Researchers have reimagined Heisenberg’s uncertainty principle, engineering a trade-off that allows precise measurement of both position and momentum
• Using quantum computing tools like grid states and trapped ions, they demonstrated sensing precision beyond classical limits
• Such advances could revolutionize navigation, medicine, and physics

items.title: Namibia deploys army to fight wildfire burning third of Etosha game reserve
bullets: • Namibia has begun deploying hundreds of soldiers to fight a fire that has burned through a third of Etosha national park
• The park in the north of the largely desert country is home to 114 species of mammals, notably the critically endangered black rhinoceros
• The fire had been burning since 22 September and had caused extensive ecological damage

items.title: The endangered cactus behind Mexico's sweet secret
bullets: • Barches of barrel cactus have been chopped up and seeped in vats of sugar until they're crystalized
• The Mexican government began banning the sale of acitrón in the early 2000s
• The biznaga cactus was found to be in danger of extinction due to overexploitation

items.title: NoViolet Bulawayo wins the Best of Caine award
bullets: • Best of Caine Prize for African Writing is awarded for a short story
• The story examines the lives of a group of children in Budapest, Hungary
• The winner of the award will be announced at the end of the month
• The award was handed out at the British Library in London today

items.title: Tropical Storm Imelda expected to batter parts of the southeastern U.S. this week
bullets: • Parts of the U.S
• are expected to be hit by Tropical Storm I-Bahamas
• The storm is expected to bring heavy rain to parts of the country
• Parts of South Carolina, Florida and Georgia are in the path of the storm
• The hurricane is a tropical depression

items.title: Is taking acetaminophen during pregnancy really associated with autism in children?
bullets: • President Trump suggested that taking acetaminophen during pregnancy is linked to autism in children
• Doctors disagree and say there's no strong evidence for that
• Tylenol could play a role in ongoing legal cases against the company that makes it
• NPR's pharmaceuticals correspondent, Sydney Lupkin, joins us in the comments

items.title: Meteorite collectors gather in Cincinnati this weekend for 'Meet a Meteorite'
bullets: • Meteorite collectors gather in Cincinnati this weekend for 'Meet a Meteorite' The rocks that hurtle from outer space and make it to Earth get a moment to shine
• At the Cincinnati Observatory later today, collectors will be showing off some of their treasures

items.title: How Kyrsten Sinema's decision makes Democrats' 2024 Senate map tighter
bullets: • Arizona Sen
• Kyrsten Sinema has always been a thorn in the Democrats side during her time in Congress
• She voted against her party more than almost any other member of Congress
• Now, the Democratic caucus has 48 Democrats and three independents

items.title: ‘I think we’re headed to a shutdown,’ says JD Vance as Mike Johnson calls for more time for negotiations – live
bullets: • House speaker Mike Johnson wants more time for negotiations as JD Vance blames Democrats over potential shutdown
• Governor of Illinois said Monday it appeared the federal government would deploy 100 troops to protect U.S
• Immigration and Customs Enforcement personnel and facilities
• An immigration processing center has been the site of frequent protests and aggressive tactics by federal agents

items.title: Wealthfront files for IPO, joining wave of fintech firms going public in 2025
bullets: • Wealthfront filed for a U.S
• initial public offering Monday
• The company helped popularize the robo-advisor style of automated investing
• It's the latest in a wave of fintech firms going public this year
• Wealthfront, led by CEO David Fortunato, had $88.2 billion in assets on its platform

items.title: Trump talks with Democrats fail to yield breakthrough as US shutdown nears
bullets: • Democrats are refusing to support GOP legislation to keep government open beyond Tuesday unless it includes several healthcare provisions
• Republican leaders of the Senate and House of Representatives also met in the Oval Office on Monday
• But there was little sign that Republicans had shifted from their demands that Senate Democrats vote for their bill that would keep the government open

items.title: Anthropic says its new AI model “maintained focus” for 30 hours on multistep tasks
bullets: • Anthropic releases Claude Sonnet 4.5, a new AI language model
• Anthropic calls it its "most capable model to date" with improved coding and computer use capabilities
• The company also released Claude Code 2.0, a command-line AI agent for developers, and the Claude Agent SDK

items.title: Trump and Netanyahu agree new US peace plan for Gaza
bullets: • US President Donald Trump and Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu agree new peace plan for Gaza
• Plan would see Hamas release of more than two dozen hostages and end military operations
• Plan demands that Hamas has no role in governing Gaza, and leaves the door open for an eventual Palestinian state

items.title: Sports piracy site Streameast returns after US government let domain expire
bullets: • Homeland Security Investigations (HSI) seized several domains belonging to the Streameast piracy network in August 2024
• After the seizure, trying to access those sites resulted in a pop-up from HSI stating, ‘THIS DOMAIN HAS BEEN SEIZED.”

items.title: 'We're headed to a shutdown,' Vance says after Trump meeting with leaders ends
bullets: • Vice President JD Vance: "I think we're headed to a shutdown because the Democrats won't do the right thing" Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer and House Minority Leader Hakeem Jeffries met with President Donald Trump at the White House on Monday
• The meeting comes less than two days before the government will begin in the absence of a funding deal

items.title: Startup founder Charlie Javice sentenced to 7 years in prison for defrauding JPMorgan Chase
bullets: • Charlie Javice is sentenced to 85 months in prison for defrauding JPMorgan Chase
• The 33-year-old founder of a fintech startup was found guilty in March of fraud
• Prosecutors had sought a sentence of 12 years
• "I will spend my entire life regretting these errors," Javice says

items.title: Des Moines revokes education license of school superintendent arrested by Ice
bullets: • Ian Roberts, the superintendent of Iowa’s largest school district, was arrested last week by US Immigration and Customs Enforcement (Ice) agents
• He was found in possession of a loaded handgun and the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives is investigating how he obtained it

items.title: EA will be a very different company under private ownership
bullets: • Electronic Arts plans to sell itself to a consortium of private equity firms
• The $55 billion deal is the largest leveraged buyout in history
• The new owners will be saddled with roughly $20 billion of new debt
• The company will be on the hook for roughly $1 billion a year in service payments on that debt

items.title: US whistleblowers say they were fired for raising fair housing concerns
bullets: • The White House is preparing to launch a new program to help Americans with disabilities
• The program aims to help people with disabilities in the United States
• It is the first time the White House has been asked to make a public announcement about the program
• The government has been forced to withdraw from the program after it was revealed

items.title: Madagascar's president dissolves government after 'Gen Z' protests
bullets: • Madagascar president Andry Rajoelina dissolves government after 'Gen-Z' protests
• Protests have seen thousands of predominantly young demonstrators take to the streets in cities across the country
• UN's human rights chief says 22 people have been killed and 100 others injured

items.title: Government shutdowns usually have little economic impact. This time could be different
bullets: • Government shutdowns historically have left little mark other than political damage
• Most economists calculate the impact as about 0.1 percentage point off gross domestic product for week
• If Trump follows through on the threat, it throws a wrench into what otherwise have been more political than economic events

items.title: Entrepreneur Charlie Javice sentenced to over seven years for defrauding JPMorgan
bullets: • Charlie Javice convicted of defrauding JPMorgan Chase into buying her college financial aid startup Frank for $175m
• Prosecutors had sought a 12-year prison sentence for bank fraud, securities fraud, wire fraud and conspiracy
• JPMorgan CEO Jamie Dimon called buying Frank a “huge mistake”

items.title: Afghanistan telecom blackout as Taliban shuts off internet
bullets: • Afghanistan telecom blackout as Taliban shuts off internet services across the country
• The Taliban have imposed a nationwide ban on internet traffic in accordance with their Islamic law
• Many people will not notice the impact until Tuesday morning, when services are expected to resume
• Mobile internet and satellite TV also affected

items.title: YouTube agrees to pay Trump $24 million to settle lawsuit over Jan. 6 suspension
bullets: • YouTube agrees to pay Trump $24.5 million to settle lawsuit over Jan
• YouTube parent company Google will dedicate $22 million of the settlement toward the construction of a $200 million Mar-a-Lago-style ballroom in the White House
• It's the latest settlement reached by a tech company sued by Trump in the wake of the Capitol riots
• Free speech experts have said the suits brought by Trump did not raise credible legal claims

items.title: F-Droid says Google’s new sideloading restrictions will kill the project
bullets: • F-Droid is the largest app store for Android software
• Google recently announced plans to force app developers to verify their apps
• Apps that have not been validated by the company will not be installed on any Android device
• F-Froid says the move will not stop apps from being installed in the Play Store

items.title: Madagascar’s president dissolves government amid youth-led protests
bullets: • President Andry Rajoelina has dissolved the government after youth-led protests over water and power cuts
• The UN says 22 people have been killed and more than 100 injured in three days of demonstrations
• Thousands of people have marched in the capital Antananarivo since demonstrations began last week

items.title: Democrats refuse to cave on health care before meeting with Trump on government shutdown
bullets: • House Democratic Leader Hakeem Jeffries: "Enough with the games that Republicans have been playing connected to the health care of the American people" Republicans insist that any deal must extend enhanced Obamacare tax credits that are due to expire at the end of 2025
• At least seven Senate Democrats would need to vote with Republicans to pass legislation

items.title: ESA will pay an Italian company nearly $50 million to design a mini-Starship
bullets: • The European Space Agency signs a deal with Avio to design a reusable upper stage
• The deal is part of an effort to replicate SpaceX's success with the Falcon 9
• The European deal is worth $47 million and is the latest in a long line of work done by SpaceX

items.title: Wildfire in Namibia is contained, says PM, after criticism of response
bullets: • The fire broke out in Etosha national park, in Namibia's north, on 22 September
• The government said it suspected charcoal production next to the park was to blame
• It said 49 soldiers were being deployed to fight the fires and a further 500 on Sunday

items.title: A year after Helene, a group of raft guides embarks on a river clean-up mission
bullets: • A year after Hurricane Helene, a group of raft guides embarks on a river clean-up mission

• Flooding forced most rafting companies to cease operations, except for the Nolichucky River

items.title: West Africans deported from US to Ghana ‘dumped without documents in Togo’
bullets: • Eight to 10 west African nationals have been forcibly sent by Ghana to Togo, bypassing a formal border crossing, and then left on the street without passports
• Up to 28 people have arrived in the west African nation from the US so far in the deportation programme

items.title: Trump considering supplying Ukraine with long-range missiles, Vance says
bullets: • US Vice-President JD Vance says President Donald Trump will make "final determination" on the matter
• Vance says Tomahawk missiles have a range of 2,500 km (1,500 miles) US special envoy to Ukraine, Keith Kellogg, seemed to suggest Trump has already authorised strikes deep into Russian territory

items.title: Lesotho's Famo music: from shepherd songs to gang wars
bullets: • Lesotho's Famo music is a popular genre of pastoral accordion music beloved by the country's people
• Puseletso Seema is known as "the Queen of Famo" but her living conditions are far from regal
• Famo is a music that is emotionally connected, you can express your happiness, sadness, all your feelings

items.title: Comic Cristela Alonzo grew up in fear of border patrol. ICE has 'brought it all back'
bullets: • Comic Cristela Alonzo grew up in an abandoned diner in Texas
• Her mother, a Mexican immigrant, left an abusive marriage to her daughter

• government in Washington, DC

items.title: Compass-Anywhere real estate merger could squeeze small brokerages

items.title: Police say 'everyone has been accounted for' in Michigan church attack that killed 4
bullets: • Police say 'everyone has been accounted for' in Michigan church attack that killed 4 and injured 8

• The FBI is investigating the attack as an "act of targeted violence" The attack unfolded Sunday morning during a Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints service

items.title: Trump announces an agreement with Israel to end war in Gaza
bullets: • Trump announces an agreement with Israel to end war in Gaza
• President Trump and Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu appeared together at the White House Monday
• The announcement of a peace plan comes as the two-year anniversary of the Hamas attack on Israel draws closer
• A growing list of nations recognized Palestinian statehood last week

items.title: Moldova's pro-EU party wins vote mired in claims of Russian interference
bullets: • Moldova's pro-EU party wins vote mired in claims of Russian interference
• Maia Sandu's Party of Action and Solidarity secured about 50% of the vote

items.title: The latest on the Michigan church shooting. And, Trump's new plan to end war in Gaza
bullets: • The latest on the Michigan church shooting
• An unknown number of people are unaccounted for
• The gunman, 40-year-old Thomas Jacob Sanford, was killed after exchanging gunfire with two law enforcement officers
• Four top congressional leaders, two from each party, are scheduled to meet with President Trump today

items.title: Overseas Hong Kong pro-democracy activist Nathan Law denied entry to Singapore
bullets: • Hong Kong activist Nathan Law says he was denied entry to Singapore for what he presumes were political reasons
• Law is one of a number of Hong Kong activists who have left the city in recent years
• Hong Kong police have issued a warrant for Law's arrest under the city's National Security Law

items.title: Scared of spiders? Some former arachnophobes now are keeping jumping spiders as pets
bullets: • Thousands of jumping spiders are being flooded with requests from people who want to keep them as pets
• Social media videos of the spiders' antics have been viewed millions of times on YouTube
• Some women are trying to overcome their fear of spiders, while others are simply enchanted by their unexpected cuteness

items.title: Hubble finds a hybrid galaxy with a mysterious and violent past
bullets: • Hubble finds a hybrid galaxy with a mysterious and violent past
• NGC 2775 lies 67 million light-years away in the constellation Cancer (The Crab) Blending features of spirals, ellipticals, and lenticulars, its structure may be the result of past galactic mergers

items.title: Earth was born dry until a cosmic collision made it a blue planet
bullets: • Earth was born dry until a cosmic collision made it a blue planet
• Initially, the planet was barren and inhospitable, missing water and carbon compounds
• A colossal collision with Theia likely changed everything, bringing the essential ingredients for life
• Study highlights that habitability may hinge on rare chance events

items.title: Black hole discovery confirms Einstein and Hawking were right
bullets: • New observations of a merger of two black holes confirm decades-old predictions by Albert Einstein, Stephen Hawking and Roy Kerr
• Scientists tracked the complete cosmic collision, confirming that black holes are defined by mass and spin
• They also gained stronger proof that a black hole’s event horizon only grows, echoing thermodynamic laws

items.title: Fossils in germany reveal a Jurassic sea monster with a swordfish snout
bullets: • Fossils in germany reveal a Jurassic sea monster with a swordfish snout
• Discovery underscores Mistelgau’s global significance as a Jurassic fossil site
• The marine reptile had a dramatic overbite similar to swordfish and unique skeletal traits that set it apart from other species

items.title: YouTube caves to Trump with $24.5 million settlement
bullets: • YouTube has settled a lawsuit President Donald Trump filed against the company in 2021
• Trump filed sweeping lawsuits against Google-owned YouTube, Meta (then Facebook) and X (then Twitter) after he was suspended from the platforms
• YouTube, like Meta and X, is paying to end Trump’s lawsuit over content moderation decisions following the January 6th insurrection at the Capitol

items.title: SB 53, the landmark AI transparency bill, is now law in California
bullets: • Senate Bill 53, the landmark AI transparency bill, is now law in California
• The hotly-debated legislation establishes safety reporting requirements for large AI companies
• It's the second draft of such a bill, as California governor Gavin Newsom vetoed the first version last year

items.title: Microsoft is bringing its Windows engineering teams back together again
bullets: • Microsoft is bringing its Windows engineering teams back together again
• The unified team is meant to support Microsoft’s work on top priorities like AI
• This is the first major Windows reorg since Pavan Davuluri was promoted to Windows and Surface chief

items.title: Tile’s lack of encryption could make tracker owners vulnerable to stalking
bullets: • Security researchers are shining the spotlight on a serious security vulnerability that could enable stalkers to track victims using their own Tile tags

• Bad actors could also potentially intercept unencrypted information sent from the tags, like their unique IDs and MAC addresses, and track their movements using other Bluetooth devices or an antenna

items.title: What EA’s buyout might mean for its future
bullets: • Electronic Arts announced that it is going to be acquired and taken private in a massive $55 billion deal

• The deal is expected to close in Q1 of EA’s 2027 fiscal year (which takes place from April 1 to June 30th, 2026) It could have massive ramifications for the company, the types of games it invests in and the people that make them
